  <mads:note type="source">mith's Dictionary of Greek and Roman Biography and Mythology, Vol 2, 1867, p. 14: "Emporius, was a Latin rhetorician 
    and the author of three short tracts entitled De Ethopoeia ac Loco Communi Liber, Demonstrativae Maleteriae
    praeceptum and De Deliberatia Specie. He is believed to have flourished not earlier than the sixth century, 
    chiefly from the circumstance that he refers in his illustrations to the regal power rather than to the imperial dignity, 
    which he would scarcely have done had he lived before the revival of the kingly title...."</mads:note>
